      "message": "[critical] Line 140: 🔴 Downcasting to `HardwareServiceImpl` breaks abstraction and couples the Fragment to a concrete implementation. If the injected `HardwareService` is ever a mock or a different impl (e.g. in tests), this silently does nothing. Instead, add `getCurrentCameraZoomRange()` and `setCurrentCameraZoom()` to the `HardwareService` interface (or to the Presenter layer) so the Fragment never needs to know about `HardwareServiceImpl`.\n\nThis same downcast appears in the double-tap detector (line 151) and the preview touch listener (line 651/652). All three should be fixed.",
