      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 673: 🟡 `applyZoom` early-returns when `ratio \u003c\u003d 1f`, which means if the user was previously zoomed and then double-taps to reset to 1.0, the zoom reset won\u0027t be applied via `CONTROL_ZOOM_RATIO` or `SCALER_CROP_REGION`. On pre-R devices, an old crop region could persist. Remove or change the guard to `if (ratio \u003d\u003d 1f \u0026\u0026 /* no previous zoom */)` or always apply the zoom setting.\n\n```suggestion\n        if (ratio \u003c\u003d 1f) {\n            // Still need to explicitly reset crop/zoom if it was previously set.\n            if (Build.VERSION.SDK_INT \u003e\u003d Build.VERSION_CODES.R) {\n                builder.set(CaptureRequest.CONTROL_ZOOM_RATIO, 1f)\n            }\n            return\n        }\n```",
      "revId": "ad1881c5ee77532564265ba20893c3a148345a89",
