      "message": "[warning] Line 133: 🟡 `setPinchToZoomEnabled(true)` is called unconditionally on every layout pass for every participant, but there is no corresponding `false` path or cleanup. This means:\n1. Each call creates a new `VideoDisplayZoomHelper` and re-attaches a touch listener if the zoom helper was previously null (first call is fine, but the intent is unclear).\n2. More importantly, zoom is enabled for *all* remote participant views including small grid tiles where pinch-to-zoom is likely unwanted and may interfere with other touch gestures (e.g. tap-to-focus a participant).\n\nConsider enabling it only for the active/focused participant: `setPinchToZoomEnabled(i.active \u0026\u0026 !pipMode)`.",
